"{\"uid\": \"cityam.com-novak-djokovic-career-achievements-after-winning-paris-2024-olympic-games-gold\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"Featured  Submit a story  Tell us your story.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 45, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Featured  Submit a story  Tell us your story.\", \"from\": 47, \"to\": 92, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Featured  Submit a story  Tell us your story.\", \"from\": 94, \"to\": 139, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"By:Matt Hardy  Deputy Sports Editor - City AM  Novak Djokovic became just the fifth tennis player to complete the career Golden Slam after beating Spaniard Carlos Alcaraz 7-6 7-6 yesterday in the men's singles final at the Paris 2024 Olympic Games.\", \"from\": 141, \"to\": 389, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 144, \"end\": 154, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Matt_Hardy\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Matt Hardy\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q13474373\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Matt_Hardy\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Matt_Hardy\"}, {\"begin\": 188, \"end\": 202, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Novak_Djokovic\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Novak Djokovic\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10833314\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Novak_Djokovic\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Novak_Djokovic\"}, {\"begin\": 288, \"end\": 296, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Spaniards\", \"score\": 0.9451758660276807, \"rank\": 0.057931889722937134, \"text\": \"Spaniard\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Spaniards\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Spaniards\"}, {\"begin\": 297, \"end\": 311, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Carlos_Alcaraz\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Carlos Alcaraz\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10833314\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Carlos_Alcaraz\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Carlos_Alcaraz\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He joinsSteffi Graf, Andre Agassi, Rafael Nadal and Sarena Williams in the exclusive club made up of players who have won the four annual Grand Slams - Australian Open, French Open, Wimbledon and US Open - as well as an Olympic gold.\", \"from\": 391, \"to\": 624, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 587, \"end\": 594, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/US_Open_(tennis)\", \"score\": 0.935861658826044, \"rank\": 0.027464247762228403, \"text\": \"US Open\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/US_Open_(tennis)\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/US_Open_(tennis)\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"His 21-year-old opponent forced two tie-breaks but the veteran 37-year-old finally won his first Olympic title.\", \"from\": 626, \"to\": 737, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"It comes just three weeks after Alcaraz beat Djokovic in straight sets at the final of Wimbledon in London.\", \"from\": 739, \"to\": 846, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 771, \"end\": 778, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alcaraz\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 9.453070173569284e-16, \"text\": \"Alcaraz\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\", \"Q3957\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alcaraz\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alcaraz\"}, {\"begin\": 839, \"end\": 845, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London\", \"score\": 0.9884781328893295, \"rank\": 0.011621484570002658, \"text\": \"London\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The Serbian, who has 24 Grand Slam titles to his name, claimed his first singles title at an Olympic Games at his fifth Olympics having won a bronze in 2008 and lost bronze medal matches in 2012 and 2021.\", \"from\": 848, \"to\": 1052, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 852, \"end\": 859, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/reso